text: Leave everything behind that isn’t currently serving you. Don’t try to reach it out of habit or comfort.

author: ❀♡︎ princessa ayón ❀♥︎
text:
I destroyed the old version of myself. 
Sometimes I try to reach back out into the past to fill in the *emptiness*, but I much rather slowly morph into the next version of myself. Fill in the space with the now & not look back. 🌓🦋

author: ❀♡︎ princessa ayón ❀♥︎
text: I don’t want anything. I’m out here just existing, floating. At peace. ☮︎︎

author: ❀♡︎ princessa ayón ❀♥︎
text: People talk too much. In reality nothing anyone says matters. Life just is. Don’t try to analyze anything, you’ll take the fun out of it. Detach & observe.

author: ❀♡︎ princessa ayón ❀♥︎
text: I’m really crying. Baking is my passion & I can’t believe I let others tell me not to pursue that as a career. I feel so alive. I know who I am, never doubting myself ever again. I’m so happy baking cakes & bread!👩🏻‍🍳🥛🎂🤍

author: ❀♡︎ princessa ayón ❀♥︎
text: Literally crying, I feel like I’m doing everything I’m supposed to be doing in this lifetime. I really wanted to be this version of me when I was younger & now here I am living it. 🐻🤎🤍

author: ❀♡︎ princessa ayón ❀♥︎
text: I seriously love Chef Orlando, I can’t believe I get to spend a year in this baking & pastry program. I want to cry. My soul feels like it’s singing, no doubt in my heart this was meant to be in my path. I’m surrounded by talented people who appreciate baking as an art. 🧁🥺
